data.description: Are you looking for that downtown lifestyle without sacrificing suburban life too? This home is a five-minute drive to Tropicana Field and downtown St. Pete, with all the amazing shops and restaurants along vibrant Central Avenue, and steps away from Woodlawn Park! This two-bedroom, 1-bath bungalow is truly in the heart of St. Pete. It is completely move-in ready with all the main elements of the home taken care of so you can enjoy a low-maintenance lifestyle. When you walk in, you’ll notice a flexible space that can be used as a sitting room or office. The living room is large and open to the dining and kitchen area so you can entertain easily. Step outside to enjoy a spacious back patio and huge yard. There is plenty of space to build that pool you’ve been dreaming of or even build on an addition in the future. This home is also zoned for adding an ADU. This home has had all the updates in the last few years like newer roof, HVAC system, windows, exterior stucco and paint, landscaping, remodeled bathroom and a brand new water heater. Alley access gives you even more options to store your toys like a boat or RV, and the RV hook ups are already installed for convenience. Across the street is Woodlawn Park with several sports fields including beach volleyball which you can see right from your front yard. If you’re ready to enjoy all that St. Pete has to offer, this is the home for you!
